        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Vehicles with optional Heater Shutoff Valve, Code 16554, may exhibit kinking of the heater hose
                    and reduced heater performance (See Figure 1).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0116081" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0116081.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. With The Old-Style Valve (Arrow) On Vehicles Built Before 09/27/2001</caption>
                </figure>
                <para>A new shutoff valve with a 45&#176; elbow is now in production and can be used to repair earlier
                    vehicles that exhibit kinking of the heater hose (See Figure 2).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0116082" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G0116082.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="502px"
                             scalefitheight="352px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. With The New-Style Valve And 45&#176; Elbow For Vehicles Built After 09/27/2001
                    </caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. New shutoff valve, 388668C91, installed with outlet pointed rearward and phased 30&#176;
                            toward centerline of vehicle.
                        </callout1>
                        <callout1>2. 45&#176; elbow, 864450R1, installed pointing towards centerline of vehicle and
                            phased 45&#176; upward.
                        </callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
